data.Name: Laser Scanner
data.Description: Laser scanning is a technology and methodology used for capturing detailed three-dimensional (3D) representations of objects, environments, or surfaces using laser beams.

data.Name: Radar Altimeter
data.Description: A radar altimeter, also known as a radio altimeter, is an instrument used to measure the distance between an aircraft or satellite and the Earth's surface, or another target object, directly below it. This technology operates based on radar principles and provides accurate and continuous altitude information.

data.Name: GPS
data.Description: GPS, or Global Positioning System, is a satellite-based navigation system that provides precise location and tracking worldwide. It works by receiving signals from multiple satellites to calculate your 3D position (latitude, longitude, and altitude).
